      \field{labeltitlesource}{title}
      \field{abstract}{Cyber Threat Intelligence (CTI) programs have gained momentum across the cybersecurity community. Whether they are vendor based or open source solutions, practitioners should be able to find an appropriate solution to enhance security for their IT infrastructure. The tangible world, i.e. (Industrial) Internet of Things (I)IoT products and embedded components have not been considered yet in the CTI world with few exceptions from industry-specific vendors and Information Sharing Analysis Centres (ISACs). This extended abstract presents a work in progress to establish a CTI program for ``things'', especially the generation, consumption and distribution of product-specific CTI.}
